import PIL
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw, ImageFont
from PIL import ImageEnhance

# read image and convert to RGB
image=Image.open("readonly/msi_recruitment.gif")
image=image.convert('RGB')

#create object to draw
draw = ImageDraw.Draw(image)
w, h = image.size

#text font and size
font = ImageFont.truetype("readonly/fanwood-webfont.ttf", 25)



#assignment1 here
nl = []

for c in (0.1, 0.5, 0.9):

    ch0_txt = "channel 0 intensity {}".format(c)
    #print(ch0_txt)
    #text_w, text_h = draw.textsize(ch0_txt, font)

    #split rgb into 3 channels
    r, g, b = image.split()
    #adjust intensity
    r = r.point(lambda i: i * c)
    result = Image.merge('RGB', (r, g, b))
    result = result.resize((int(result.width / 2), (int(result.height / 2))))
    re = Image.new('RGB', (result.width, 30), color = (0, 0, 0))
    d = ImageDraw.Draw(re)
    d.text((10, 10), ch0_txt, font=font, fill=result.getpixel((0, 50)))
    sheet = PIL.Image.new(result.mode, (result.width, result.height + re.height))
    sheet.paste(re, (0, result.height))
    sheet.paste(result, (0, 0))
    nl.append(sheet)
    
    
    
for c in (0.1, 0.5, 0.9):
    #green channel
    ch1_txt = "channel 1 intensity {}".format(c)
    #text_w, text_h = draw.textsize(ch1_txt, font)
    #split rgb into 3 channels
    r, g, b = image.split()
    #adjust intensity
    g = g.point(lambda i: i * c)
    result = Image.merge('RGB', (r, g, b))
    result = result.resize((int(result.width / 2), (int(result.height / 2))))
    re = Image.new('RGB', (result.width, 30), color = (0, 0, 0))
    d = ImageDraw.Draw(re)
    d.text((10, 10), ch1_txt, font=font, fill=result.getpixel((0, 50)))
    sheet = PIL.Image.new(result.mode, (result.width, result.height + re.height))
    sheet.paste(re, (0, result.height))
    sheet.paste(result, (0, 0))
    nl.append(sheet)
    
    

    
    
for c in (0.1, 0.5, 0.9):
    #blue channel
    ch2_txt = "channel 2 intensity {}".format(c)
    #text_w, text_h = draw.textsize(ch2_txt, font)
    #split rgb into 3 channels
    r, g, b = image.split()
    #adjust intensity
    b = b.point(lambda i: i * c)
    result = Image.merge('RGB', (r, g, b))
    result = result.resize((int(result.width / 2), (int(result.height / 2))))
    re = Image.new('RGB', (result.width, 30), color = (0, 0, 0))
    d = ImageDraw.Draw(re)
    d.text((10, 10), ch2_txt, font=font, fill=result.getpixel((0, 50)))
    sheet = PIL.Image.new(result.mode, (result.width, result.height + re.height))
    sheet.paste(re, (0, result.height))
    sheet.paste(result, (0, 0))
    nl.append(sheet)
    
# create a contact sheet from different brightnesses
first_image=nl[0]
contact_sheet=PIL.Image.new(first_image.mode, (first_image.width*3,first_image.height*3))
x=0
y=0

for img in nl:
    # Lets paste the current image into the contact sheet
    contact_sheet.paste(img, (x, y) )
    # Now we update our X position. If it is going to be the width of the image, then we set it to 0
    # and update Y as well to point to the next "line" of the contact sheet.
    if x+first_image.width == contact_sheet.width:
        x=0
        y=y+first_image.height
    else:
        x=x+first_image.width
        
# resize and display the contact sheet
#contact_sheet = contact_sheet.resize((int(contact_sheet.width/2),int(contact_sheet.height/2) ))
display(contact_sheet)
